Understanding User Engagement with Pinterest Boards

Goal: Analyze how users interact with Pinterest’s board and saving features to uncover pain points, engagement trends, and potential product improvements.

Methods:
	•	Conduct 5–10 structured interviews with active Pinterest users about saving habits, board organization, and frustrations.
	•	Run a survey to gather quantitative insights on how users revisit saved content.
	•	Perform thematic analysis to identify behavioral patterns in how users categorize, return to, and take action on their saved ideas.

Deliverables:
	•	A research report summarizing key findings, insights, and product recommendations.
	•	Data visualizations highlighting engagement trends, common behaviors, and areas for improvement.
	•	A presentation deck to communicate findings in an actionable way for product teams.
